1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with MIMO (Multiple Input Multiple Output) systems and their lattices, which are important in information theory. 
2. cs.NT (Number Theory) - The paper uses results from class field theory and discusses the discriminant of a maximal order, which are topics in number theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions QAM (Quadrature Amplitude Modulation) coefficients, which are used in cryptography and security. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses an algorithm for finding maximal orders within a cyclic division algebra and enhancements to this algorithm, which are topics in data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with MIMO systems, which are also studied in systems and control.
